# --- HMDG Astro Base Template - _redirects ---
#
# Cloudflare Pages routes file. Lines without a leading "#" are
# treated as redirect rules; lines starting with "#" are comments.
#
# Format:  <source>  <destination>  <status>
#
# Valid status codes on Cloudflare Pages:
#   200 (rewrite, keeps URL)
#   301 (permanent redirect)
#   302 (temporary redirect — default if status omitted)
#   303 (see other)
#   307 (temporary redirect, preserves method)
#   308 (permanent redirect, preserves method)
#
# NOT supported here:
#   404 / 410 - cannot be set via _redirects on Cloudflare Pages.
#               Implement via a Pages Function (e.g. functions/wp-[[path]].ts)
#               that returns a Response with status 410 + a noindex body.
#
# WordPress migration tip
#   When migrating from WordPress, old /?p=123 URLs and dead /tag/x
#   slugs should typically return 410 Gone (so Google de-indexes them
#   faster than 404). Use a Pages Function for those, not this file.
#
# Per-client examples (uncomment + adapt):
#
#   /old-services        /services           301
#   /book                /contact            302
#   /sitemap.xml         /sitemap-index.xml  301
#   /api/legacy/:slug    /api/v2/:slug       308
#
# Wildcards: use :placeholder syntax for path segments,
#            * for catch-all (one segment), :rest* for greedy.
#
# Order matters - first match wins.

# ── Rank Math "Fallback Behaviour → Redirect to Homepage" ──────────
# Implementation lives in src/middleware.ts, NOT in this file.
# Reason: Cloudflare Pages evaluates _redirects BEFORE the Astro
# Worker runs, and Wrangler's build-time prerender simulator loops
# infinitely if a wildcard catches /. The Worker already handles
# 404 fallthrough natively — middleware intercepts 404 responses
# and converts them to 301 redirects to the homepage. See
# .claude/prompts/fallback-redirect.md for the full architecture.
#
